Um... the only wizzies who are helpless after a manaburn are the people who bought the characters on ebay.<br>
<br>
you see, when arguing this point, most of the wizzies will conveniently forget about the epic/manarobe trick...<br>
<br>
If they dont have an epic.... running at jboot or run3 speed oughta get away from the greenie long enough to zone/gather/manastone/manarobe...<br>
<br>
manaburn is broken in only two aspects:<br>
1) PvP<br>
2) certain outdoor higher-end encounters<br>
<br>
for PvP:<br>
instead of nerfing it, enhance other classes so that they have a defense for it.  Change the &quot;rune&quot;, &quot;skin&quot;, and &quot;spellshield&quot; line of spells so that they absorb ALL of the blows as long as they have 1 HP left....  thus if &quot;awarrior_01&quot; has a spellshield on and only has 1HP of it left and gets manaburned, the warrior takes ZERO damage...(the spellshield is breached however)  Now, for the melee, place &quot;minor spellshield scarabs&quot; (5 charge minor-spellshield 2second cast rclick items) on the magic items vendor.  Note, certain powerful mobs might know how to cast such a spell as well!  Such a change might actually make PvP between two MB wizzies fun!<br>
<br>
for MB-farming:<br>
just lower the maximum range for manaburn to within most mobs' aggro range... the team-MB will have to work on a tad more planning....<br>
<br>
The idea is not to uber-nerf MB, as it is a cool idea... its just a tad broken due to certain dorks and how MB was implemented.<br>
<br>
