<br>
It occured to me that you have probably never MB'd a mob. This would explain a lot of the differences in out arguements, so let me fill you in on some basic rules we use to insure success. Dispute these all you want, but we came up with this after figuring out what went wrong on failed MB attempts.<br>
<br>
1. No one is allowed to use extended range or spell haste. These are an advantage so why not use them? Simple, unless everyone has both items, these will cause a wipe out. You see, what ends up happening is the person with both casts sooner and faster so the first MB will land over 2 seconds before the first MB. This is bad because it pulls agro off of the puller and causes the dragon to stop. As soon as the dragon stops, you get an AE - if the AE interupts even 1 MB, it's a failed attempt and there will more than likely be a TPW, or at least a few deaths.<br>
<br>
2. Always pull the dragon to the wizards (except Sont who is totally blind). We have tried to do as you have suggested and inched up to the dragon and cast without getting agro. In every single case we have tried this, the dragon has agro'd and killed people before MB goes off and we end up with a pissed off dragon in camp and a bunch of dead wizards.<br>
<br>
3. The puller can't be one of the wizards MBing. We always use a 5th to pull. Contrary to anything spdat says, a dragon will close what ever range MB is in actuality in less than the time it takes to cast it. You can get a mile ahead of the dragon, stop, spam the MB key until it casts, and the dragon will always get to you before MB gets to it.<br>
<br>
4. Always use an experienced MB puller. The reason the puller has to be experienced is that the dragon has to have the perfect approach or the attempt will fail. The puller can't get too far ahead -- as you found out -- or the dragon will warp on to you and wipe out the attempt. The puller has to pull very near perpendicular to the line of wizards or the attempt will fail. If the puller comes from an angle, some MBs will go off too soon and you end up with the same problem as using spell range/haste items, again failure and wipe out. Also, as someone else already mentioned, MB is a bit buggy when it comes casting it so z-axis and terrain tend to cause weird problems with MB being out of range even though the dragon is on top of you.<br>
<br>
5. Always pull the dragon passed the wizards. This is another one of the found out the hard way rules. The first few tries the puller would run right up to the wizards. This resulted in a pretty dismal success ratio. Why? Like I mentioned before, the dragon closes casting range faster than you can cast MB. As soon as the dragon gets in melee range of the puller, it stops and casts an AE. Again, 1 fear landing, or one interupted MB means the dragon wins.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind that this is what we have learned from actual in game kills. Being a long time player, you know as well as I do that what seems logical when looking at the spdat and what theoretically should happen and what actually takes place in game are 2 different things. Maybe now you can see where I am basing my agruement and the points I am trying to make. I am speaking from experience, not from what should happen according to theory.<br>
<br>
What it all comes down to is that 32k dragons are obsolete content. They are trivial to small groups of high powered players be it a group of MB wizards, or some VT equipped melees. I think that the easiest change VI could make is to move the epic drops to triggered mobs like the Ragefire encounter. I would bet this would alleviate 95% of the problems caused by MB kills. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial"><img src="http://www.bfdesigns.net/eq/wandor_sig.jpg"><br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102" target="_blank"><b>Moordian</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=353608" target="_blank"><b>Wandorfu</b></a><br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.exarch.net/"><b>Fusion of Flame</b></a></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uarlinastarbright.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arlina Starbright</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/02 12:16:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1790.topic&index=138>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Team Manaburn...blessing or Curse?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Alrighty... so any 60 would know... we agree then, and thus I would know if I had agroed... and did not while in range for a spell... you do realize this only proves my point right?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
